href="#comment-162938" title="">May 12th, 2007 at 6:33 am</a></h3><p><p>Max and Jessemoya have it right; running too many simultaneous server connections is actually antisocial.</p><p>You do know how servers get overloaded when an article gets slashdotted, or shows up near the top on a social-networking site.  If all the readers of such an article have lots of these antisocial pipelining requests, your server is much more likely to crash! The rich boys at places like CNN have the capacity to handle this, so the negative effect is actually on the blog community.</p></p></div></div><div
