class="comment-body"><h3>zkam says on <a
href="#comment-163686" title="">May 21st, 2007 at 10:24 am</a></h3><p><p>Someone mentioned that IE also has the automcomplete feature, which is true.  But Firefox is smarter about it.</p><p>First, it has the .net and .org completions as mentioned in the list, (IE6 only does .com &#8211; not sure about IE7)</p><p>Second (and this is cool), you can add to the URL by typing /whatever, and the completinon still works.<br
/> example:<br
/> tvrage/Lost  (press CTRL-Enter)<br
/> expands to<br
/> <a
href="http://www.tvrage.com/Lost" rel="nofollow">http://www.tvrage.com/Lost</a></p><p>in IE, this expands to<br
/> <a
href="http://www.tvrage/Lost.com" rel="nofollow">http://www.tvrage/Lost.com</a></p><p>which is no good.</p></p></div></div><div
