class="comment-body"><h3>P1h3r1e3d13 says on <a
href="#comment-255956" title="">November 29th, 2007 at 4:49 pm</a></h3><p><p>Actually, setting &#8220;network.http.pipelining.maxrequests&#8221; to 30 will allow you to make up to 8 simultaneous connections.</p><p>It takes values from 1 to 8.  All values above 8 are assumed to be 8.</p><p>Always check out <a
href="http://kb.mozillazine.org/Firefox_:_FAQs_:_About:config_Entries" rel="nofollow">http://kb.mozillazine.org/Fire.....ig_Entries</a> before messing with about:config.</p></p></div></div><div
