class="comment-body"><h3>P1h3r1e3d13 says on <a
href="#comment-255990" title="">November 29th, 2007 at 5:45 pm</a></h3><p><p>re: #13:<br
/> it&#8217;s easier and safer to change the cache size in Tools&gt;Options&gt;Advanced&gt;Network&gt;Cache.</p><p>about:config should be avoided if it can be done another way.</p><p>re: #14:<br
/> be aware that this can cause Firefox to restore slowly from being minimized as it is loaded back into memory.</p><p>As always, check the knowledgebase (see previous comment).</p></p></div></div><div
