class="comment-body"><h3>DlEast says on <a
href="#comment-348503" title="">March 22nd, 2010 at 10:23 am</a></h3><p><p>Sick! So useful!</p><p>Here is one of my personal favorites: Change the keyword.URL in about:config if you want to replace the &#8220;I feel lucky&#8221; Google search functionality. I prefer Chrome style, where a normal Google search is issued when typing any word in the address field.</p><p>Simply change the keyword.URL to:</p><p><a
href="http://www.google.com/webhp?hl=en#hl=en&amp;source=hp&amp;q=" rel="nofollow">http://www.google.com/webhp?hl.....=hp&amp;q=</a></p><p>Cheers!</p></p></div></div><div
